With the prices skyrocketing on Garands and K98's and even Nagants, I figure I'm never gonna get to put my WW2 collection together the way I really want, so, I might as well pass this beautiful, all matching, battle hardened and proven rifle on down the line to someone who can really appreciate her. title: For Sale/Trade:  XD 9 Subcompact / Night Sights
postcontent:
This is my XD 9 subcompact with all its accessories from the first time I bought it. It is super accurate and very concealable if you are looking for a CCW. I can carry this all day with the galco IWB holster no problem. If you want to add a laser or a flash light, the galco holster will accommodate this. I used to have the Viridian on this, which is why i got this holster. 

This is one of the only subcompact pistols where you will find that it has 13 plus round magazine and still reasonably concealable. The MP Shield, the infamous Glock, and others like it, carry less then 10rds. If ever in a shoot out, the first three shots will probably miss but the other eleven will be on target (plus one in chamber). Try doing this with a mag capacity of ten or less. This was the main reason this subcompact was so hard for me to give up, the mag capacity. 

The best part of this gun is the fact that it has night sights. The night sights are REALLY BRIGHT at NIGHT.

I will refund your money if this is not true. I was going to take the night sights off but it is now a good part of the gun. 

The only and I mean only reason I am selling this is because my new obsession with the Beretta Inox compact in 9mm.
